<div id="party-manager" class="tb-band">
  <div class="tb-band-inner">
    <div class="tb-deepdive">
      <div>
        <div class="tb-feature-num">FEATURE 01</div>
        <h3>Party Manager</h3>
        <p class="tb-deepdive-lead">Officers point <code>/party start</code> at a Google Sheet, and the roster lives there. Members sign up for weapons on the embed, officers paste assignments into the sheet, hit Sync, and Discord updates automatically — loadouts included.</p>

        <div class="tb-tabs" data-tabs>
          <button type="button" class="tb-tab is-active" data-tab-target="player">Player Flow</button>
          <button type="button" class="tb-tab" data-tab-target="officer">Officer Flow</button>
        </div>

        <ol class="tb-flowlist" data-tab-panel="player">
          <li>Click <strong>Sign Up</strong>, pick the weapon(s) you can play, and leave a note if you need one — low spec, early leave, whatever officers should know.</li>
          <li>Click Sign Up again any time to change your selection.</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Un-Sign Up</strong> to pull yourself from the sheet and the party entirely.</li>
          <li>Once officers sync, click <strong>View Loadout</strong> to see your assigned weapon and required gear.</li>
        </ol>
        <ol class="tb-flowlist" data-tab-panel="officer" hidden>
          <li>Run <code>/party start &lt;sheet URL&gt;</code> — share the sheet with the bot's service account as Editor first.</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Add Details</strong> to set the event title, UTC time, meeting place, and gear requirements.</li>
          <li>Copy signups from Column A into Column F next to their assigned weapon, then click <strong>Sync</strong>.</li>
          <li>Click <strong>End Party</strong> to close signups — parties auto-expire after 10 days, capped at 10 active per server.</li>
        </ol>

        <details class="tb-details">
          <summary>Sheet setup &amp; column layout</summary>
          <div class="tb-details-body">
            <p>Copy the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1b-jZ0mVhxWnB1H5FfGaDvcJO2D9vmJLrg5mQcMthyeY/edit?gid=0#gid=0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sheet template</a> (File → Make a copy) and share it with the bot's service account — <code>tacklebox-bot@tacklebox-489703.iam.gserviceaccount.com</code> — as <strong>Editor</strong>.</p>
            <p><strong>A–C</strong> — Player signups, written automatically. Don't edit.</p>
            <p><strong>D</strong> — Role (Tank, Healer, DPS...). <strong>E</strong> — Weapon name, one per row.</p>
            <p><strong>F</strong> — Assignments. Paste player names exactly as they appear in Column A.</p>
            <p><strong>G+</strong> — Equipment loadout; header row names the slot, cells list required items. Shown to players via View Loadout.</p>
            <p>⚠️ Don't rearrange or delete columns A–F — the bot reads fixed column positions.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>

      {{ botframe(240) }}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="loot-split" class="tb-band-light">
  <div class="tb-band-inner">
    <div class="tb-deepdive tb-deepdive-alt">
      <div>
        <div class="tb-feature-num">FEATURE 02</div>
        <h3>Loot Split</h3>
        <p class="tb-deepdive-lead">Run <code>/loot start</code> after a fight and Tacklebox posts a message members react to join. Officers can add AFK players, exclude anyone who shouldn't be there, then hit Calculate — Tacklebox works out repairs, tax, and each player's cut, and drops a payout checklist your officers (or players, if you allow it) can check off.</p>

        <div class="tb-tabs" data-tabs>
          <button type="button" class="tb-tab" data-tab-target="player">Player Flow</button>
          <button type="button" class="tb-tab is-active" data-tab-target="officer">Officer Flow</button>
        </div>

        <ol class="tb-flowlist" data-tab-panel="player" hidden>
          <li>React with any emoji to join the split — one reaction counts, no matter which emoji.</li>
          <li>Excluded by an officer override? You won't appear on the payout checklist, even if you reacted.</li>
          <li>If self-marking is enabled, click <strong>Mark Myself Paid</strong> once you've been paid.</li>
        </ol>
        <ol class="tb-flowlist" data-tab-panel="officer">
          <li>Run <code>/loot start</code> — optionally set a voice channel for the Ping button, or override the guild's tax rate.</li>
          <li>Use <strong>Player Override</strong> to add AFK players or exclude anyone — up to 40 users per list.</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Calculate</strong> and enter Total Silver, Repair Cost, and Tax Rate (pre-filled with the guild default, 35% unless changed).</li>
          <li>Work the payout checklist — mark players paid, bank the unpaid, or allow self-marking. Buttons stop responding after 1 hour.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      {{ botframe(320) }}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

